snippet.textDisplay:
my venmo is @chomonica and my email is choeyyy97@gmail.com
I am a nanny/sitter and I haven't been working for weeks since all of this started and kids got off school. My parents have a small business/retail store and never in their entire life have they taken off of work except Sundays, Thanksgiving, and Christmas. They recently had to close down their store due to state lockdown and there are going to be a lot of burdens that come with that. We not only need to get food for ourselves but have to help get groceries for both my grandparents. My birthday was also on the 23rd and it was definitely bitter sweet because obviously with everything happening it's so sad to see that there are people struggling way more than me and people losing their loved ones, but it was nice to see my parents stay home from work and be able to rest. There are probably a whole bunch of people more deserving of any amount of money, but I never really enter for 'giveaways' and it would be really cool to be picked for something like this during this time. Also if anyone is still reading this 😆 I just want to say since we are ALL struggling, we're going through it together and the best we can do is care for each other. It doesn't have to be just 'influencers' or celebrities helping out with money because every single human has an impact. I've donated to Feeding America and if you can you can also donate to anything that feels true to what you want to make an impact on - every little bit goes a long way 💞💞
